==English==
===Noun===
'''rumble''' (''Plural:'' '''rumbles''')

#A low pitched irregular noise.
#:''The '''rumble''' from passing trucks made it hard to sleep at night.''
#{{slang}} A street fight or [[brawl]].

====Translations====
*Czech: [[rachot]] ''m'' (1), [[lomoz]] ''m'' (1), [[burácení]] ''n'' (1), [[dunění]] ''n'' (1), [[pouliční rvačka]] ''f'' (2), [[pouliční bitka]] ''f'' (2)

===Verb===
'''rumble'''

#To make a low pitched noise.
#:''The machine '''rumbled''', the it stopped completely and was silent.''
#To move while making a rumbling noise.
#:''The truck '''rumbled''' over the rough road.''
#{{slang}}fight, [[brawl]].

